OL,7,FHe added: "The difference tomorrow is
OL,8,Fthat it is not likely to be as warm
OL,9,Ffor Northern Ireland, Wales or
OL,10,FScotland.
OL,12,F"The really warm air will probably be
OL,13,Fconfined to southern and eastern parts
OL,14,Fof England, with temperatures expected
OL,15,Fto peak in central parts of the
OL,16,Fcountry at around 27C."
OL,18,FParts of the UK will be warm and humid
OL,19,Fin the morning before thunderstorms
OL,20,Fand heavy rain are expected in the
OL,21,Fafternoon.
